1
00:01:56,065 --> 00:01:58,045
[ Horn Blows ]

2
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:10,357
<i>[ Shouting In Siamese ]</i>

3
00:02:10,446 --> 00:02:13,791
Come on, lads. Hurry it up.
We haven't got all day.

4
00:02:13,883 --> 00:02:15,885
[ Siamese ]

5
00:02:15,985 --> 00:02:18,465
Is that it, Captain?
Are we here?

6
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:21,263
Aye, laddie.
That's Bangkok all right.

7
00:02:21,357 --> 00:02:23,997
- Louis! Oh, Louis!
- [ Siamese ]

8
00:02:24,093 --> 00:02:26,403
- Mother, look. There's Bangkok.
- Come on. Hurry it up.

9
00:02:26,496 --> 00:02:28,806
Yes, I know.
Isn't it exciting?

10
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:30,809
- Come on, lads. Hurry it up.
- Captain!

11
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:33,210
I heard them lowering the anchor.
Is anything wrong?

12
00:02:33,303 --> 00:02:36,614
We have to wait for the afternoon tide, ma'am,
to carry us over the bar.

13
00:02:36,706 --> 00:02:38,686
Oh, I see.

14
00:02:38,775 --> 00:02:40,755
[ Sighs ]

15
00:02:42,645 --> 00:02:45,524
Will the king of Siam come down to the dock
to meet us, Mother?

16
00:02:45,615 --> 00:02:48,357
I hardly think so, dear.
Kings don't, as a rule.

17
00:02:48,451 --> 00:02:50,453
<i>[ Men Shouting In Siamese ]</i>

18
00:02:50,553 --> 00:02:52,999
[ Shouting Continues ]

19
00:02:53,089 --> 00:02:56,229
[ Siamese ] Come forward, lads.
They need help in the bow.

20
00:02:56,326 --> 00:02:58,465
Get along! Get along, lads.

21
00:03:01,164 --> 00:03:03,440
It's the royal barge.

22
00:03:07,804 --> 00:03:10,683
The king <i>is</is> coming out
to meet us.

23
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:12,775
It's not the king.
It's the Kralahome.

24
00:03:12,876 --> 00:03:15,015
<i>[ Woman ]
Who is the Kralahome?</i>

25
00:03:15,111 --> 00:03:17,057
<i>[ Captain ]</i>
<i>A sort of a prime minister.</i>

26
00:03:17,146 --> 00:03:19,956
<i>The king's right-hand man,
you might say</i>

27
00:03:20,049 --> 00:03:23,622
May I look?
Please, may I see?

28
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:25,700
All right, laddie.

29
00:03:25,788 --> 00:03:30,237
Ma'am, if I might be allowed
to offer you a word of warning...

30
00:03:30,326 --> 00:03:33,705
that man has power,
and he can use it for ye or against ye.

31
00:03:33,796 --> 00:03:36,902
Oh, you must stop worrying about me,
Captain Orton.

32
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,776
Sometimes I wonder if you know
what you're really facing-

33
00:03:39,869 --> 00:03:42,349
an Englishwoman alone
in a country like Siam.

34
00:03:42,438 --> 00:03:45,214
Oh, it doesn't matter, Captain.
I shall have work to do.

35
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:48,187
And the king has promised me
a house of my own.

36
00:03:48,278 --> 00:03:52,090
I'll have a place to bring up my boy,
as his father would've wished.

37
00:03:52,181 --> 00:03:55,651
Mother, look!
The prime minister is naked!

38
00:03:55,752 --> 00:03:59,325
Oh, don't be ridiculous, Louis.
He can't be naked.

39
00:03:59,422 --> 00:04:01,732
He's only...

40
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:03,804
half-naked.

41
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:08,605
They look so cruel, Mother.

42
00:04:08,698 --> 00:04:11,178
Father would not have liked us
to be afraid, would he?

43
00:04:11,267 --> 00:04:14,510
No, Louis. Father would not have
liked us to be afraid-

44
00:04:14,604 --> 00:04:16,675
not ever.

45
00:04:16,773 --> 00:04:20,380
- Doesn't anything ever frighten you, Mother?
- Ooh, yes. Sometimes.

46
00:04:20,476 --> 00:04:22,649
- What do you do?
- I whistle.

47
00:04:22,779 --> 00:04:25,191
Oh, that's why you whistle.

48
00:04:25,281 --> 00:04:27,921
Mm-hmm.
That's why I whistle.

49
00:04:29,619 --> 00:04:32,190
♪ Whenever I feel afraid ♪

50
00:04:32,288 --> 00:04:34,666
♪ I hold my head erect ♪

51
00:04:34,757 --> 00:04:37,203
♪ And whistle a happy tune, ♪

52
00:04:37,293 --> 00:04:42,265
♪ So no one will suspect
I'm afraid ♪

53
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:45,107
♪ While shivering in my shoes ♪

54
00:04:45,201 --> 00:04:47,772
♪ I strike a careless pose ♪

55
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:50,316
♪ And whistle a happy tune ♪

56
00:04:50,406 --> 00:04:55,480
♪ And no one ever knows
I'm afraid ♪

57
00:04:55,578 --> 00:04:58,286
♪ The result of this deception ♪

58
00:04:58,381 --> 00:05:00,827
♪ is very strange to tell ♪

59
00:05:00,917 --> 00:05:03,830
♪ For when I fool the people I fear ♪

60
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:06,491
♪ I fool myself as well! ♪

61
00:05:06,589 --> 00:05:09,160
♪ I whistle a happy tune ♪

62
00:05:09,258 --> 00:05:11,829
♪ And ev'ry single time ♪

63
00:05:11,928 --> 00:05:14,374
♪ The happiness in the tune ♪

64
00:05:14,464 --> 00:05:18,935
♪ convinces me that I'm not afraid. ♪

65
00:05:19,969 --> 00:05:22,415
♪ Make believe you're brave ♪

66
00:05:22,505 --> 00:05:25,418
♪ And the trick will take you far. ♪

67
00:05:25,508 --> 00:05:27,954
♪ You may be as brave ♪

68
00:05:28,044 --> 00:05:30,786
♪ as you make believe you are. ♪

69
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:33,258
♪ [ Whistling ]

70
00:05:33,349 --> 00:05:36,091
♪ [ Whistling ]

71
00:05:36,185 --> 00:05:39,166
[ Together ]
♪ You may be as brave ♪

72
00:05:39,255 --> 00:05:41,963
♪ as you make believe you are. ♪

73
00:05:42,058 --> 00:05:44,197
♪ [ Whistling ]

74
00:05:48,364 --> 00:05:52,312
I think that's a very good idea, Mother-
a very good idea!

75
00:05:52,402 --> 00:05:55,542
Yes, it is a good idea, isn't it?

76
00:05:55,638 --> 00:06:00,519
- I don't think I shall ever be afraid again.
- Good.

77
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:03,318
♪ The result of this deception ♪

78
00:06:03,413 --> 00:06:05,984
♪ is very strange to tell ♪

79
00:06:06,082 --> 00:06:08,790
♪ For when I fool the people I fear ♪

80
00:06:08,885 --> 00:06:10,865
♪ I fool myself as well! ♪

81
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:11,420
[ Gasps ]

82
00:06:11,421 --> 00:06:12,923
[ Gasps ]

83
00:06:13,022 --> 00:06:16,663
- Hmm.
- ♪ [ Whistling Together ]

84
00:06:20,029 --> 00:06:22,009
<i>[ Man Shouts In Siamese ]</i>

85
00:06:29,872 --> 00:06:33,718
[ Siamese ]
Mrs. Anna Leonowens.

86
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:37,280
Mrs. Leonowens, may I present
His Excellency, the Kralahome?

87
00:06:37,380 --> 00:06:40,691
[ Siamese ]

88
00:06:40,783 --> 00:06:45,528
Sir, you are lady who will be schoolmistress
of royal children?

89
00:06:45,621 --> 00:06:47,760
- Yes.
- He called you "sir."

90
00:06:47,857 --> 00:06:51,327
- Hush, dear. Hush.
- Have you friends in Bangkok?

91
00:06:51,427 --> 00:06:53,907
I know no one in Bangkok at all.

92
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:58,206
- [ Siamese ]
- [ Siamese ]

93
00:07:00,269 --> 00:07:03,944
His Excellency wishes to know,
are you married, sir?

94
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,951
I am a widow.

95
00:07:06,042 --> 00:07:09,683
What manner of man,
your deceased husband?

96
00:07:09,779 --> 00:07:13,226
My husband was an officer
of Her Majesty's army in-

97
00:07:15,084 --> 00:07:17,064
Tell your master
his business with me...

98
00:07:17,153 --> 00:07:19,531
is in my capacity as schoolteacher
to the royal children.

99
00:07:19,622 --> 00:07:22,796
<i>He has no right to pry
into my personal affairs.</i>

100
00:07:22,892 --> 00:07:25,270
No. Well, he hasn't, Captain Orton.

101
00:07:25,361 --> 00:07:29,002
[ Siamese ]

102
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:33,606
- Oh!
- I don't like that man.

103
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:37,617
In foreign country,
is best you like everyone until you leave.

104
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:41,280
Well, you might at least have told us
you speak English, Your Excellency.

105
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:45,689
Is not necessary for schoolteacher
to know everything at once.

106
00:07:45,781 --> 00:07:50,287
You come with me now.
Your baggages shall be carried to palace later.

107
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:52,832
Oh, just a minute.
Not the palace.

108
00:07:52,922 --> 00:07:54,833
I am not living in the palace.

109
00:07:54,924 --> 00:07:57,871
- Who say?
- The king say- uh, says.

110
00:07:57,960 --> 00:08:01,203
In his letter of agreement,
he promised me £20 a month...

111
00:08:01,297 --> 00:08:03,743
and a house of my own
outside the palace walls.

112
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:06,973
King do not always remember
what he promise.

113
00:08:07,069 --> 00:08:09,310
Then you will have to remind him.

114
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:13,251
If I tell king he break this promise,
I will make anger in him.

115
00:08:13,342 --> 00:08:17,688
I think is better if king's anger reserved
for more important matters.

116
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:21,250
Very well then.
If you are afraid to tell him, I will.

117
00:08:21,350 --> 00:08:24,024
I should like to see him at once,
while there is still time...

118
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:26,430
for me to return to England,
on this boat if necessary.

119
00:08:26,522 --> 00:08:28,433
King very busy now.

120
00:08:28,524 --> 00:08:31,767
Your Excellency, all I want is
a few minutes' audience with him.

121
00:08:31,861 --> 00:08:34,637
I have come here to work,
and I intend to work...

122
00:08:34,730 --> 00:08:38,177
but I shall take nothing less
than I have been promised.

123
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:42,909
- You will tell king this.
- I will tell king this.

124
00:08:43,005 --> 00:08:46,214
It should be very interesting meeting.

125
00:08:46,309 --> 00:08:49,188
You come now!

126
00:08:49,278 --> 00:08:51,258
If you wish to change your mind, ma'am-

127
00:08:51,347 --> 00:08:54,157
Good-bye, Captain Orton,
and thank you for everything.

128
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,389
- Good luck, ma'am.
- Good-bye, Captain.

129
00:08:56,485 --> 00:08:59,466
Good-bye, laddie.
Take good care of your mother now.

130
00:09:04,660 --> 00:09:06,799
♪ [ Whistling Together ]

131
00:09:14,036 --> 00:09:16,516
[ Trumpeting ]

132
00:09:25,381 --> 00:09:28,362
<i>[ Animal Screeching ]</i>

133
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,254
[ Chattering ]

134
00:10:11,927 --> 00:10:13,907
[ Elephant Trumpets ]

135
00:10:52,868 --> 00:10:55,849
King in bad spirit today.

136
00:10:55,938 --> 00:10:59,181
Suggest schoolteacher wait
for better day.

137
00:10:59,275 --> 00:11:02,848
My spirit is just as bad, Your Excellency.
I cannot wait.

138
00:11:02,945 --> 00:11:04,925
<i>[ Gong Sounds ]</i>

139
00:11:31,474 --> 00:11:35,923
Man is Lun Tha,
emissary from court of Burma.

140
00:11:36,011 --> 00:11:39,584
He bring present to king
from prince of Burma.

141
00:11:39,682 --> 00:11:42,128
Her name is Tuptim.

142
00:11:42,218 --> 00:11:44,528
What, that girl is a present?

143
00:11:45,621 --> 00:11:47,623
For king.

144
00:11:49,925 --> 00:11:51,905
[ Snaps Fingers ]

145
00:12:18,854 --> 00:12:21,095
King is pleased with her.

146
00:12:30,466 --> 00:12:33,379
<i>[ Gong Sounds ]</i>

147
00:12:33,469 --> 00:12:35,949
Sorry. King has concluded audience.

148
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:39,312
Well, you mean I cannot see him?

149
00:12:39,408 --> 00:12:41,388
Not today.

150
00:12:42,611 --> 00:12:44,989
Louis, come with me.

151
00:12:46,949 --> 00:12:49,259
[ Men Muttering ]

152
00:12:49,351 --> 00:12:52,298
You cannot do this.

153
00:12:57,526 --> 00:12:59,506
- Your Majesty.
- Who, who, who?

154
00:12:59,595 --> 00:13:02,474
Your Majesty,
is new English schoolteacher...

155
00:13:02,565 --> 00:13:04,806
Mrs. Anna Leonowens, and son.

156
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:06,880
Louis Leonowens.

157
00:13:08,938 --> 00:13:11,179
You are schoolteacher?

158
00:13:11,273 --> 00:13:13,844
Yes, Your Majesty,
but before I start my work here...

159
00:13:13,943 --> 00:13:16,082
there is one point about our agreement
which I would-

160
00:13:16,178 --> 00:13:18,089
You are part of general plan I have...

161
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:21,718
for bringing to Siam
what is good in Western culture.

162
00:13:21,817 --> 00:13:25,060
Already I have bring
printing press here for printing.

163
00:13:25,154 --> 00:13:27,896
- Yes, I know, Your Majesty.
- How you know?

164
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:30,368
Before I signed our agreement...

165
00:13:30,459 --> 00:13:33,599
I found out all I could about
Your Majesty's ambitions for Siam.

166
00:13:33,696 --> 00:13:35,676
Ha.

167
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:41,045
How old shall you be?

168
00:13:41,136 --> 00:13:43,707
You do not look like scientific person
for teaching of school.

169
00:13:43,806 --> 00:13:46,616
How old shall you be?

170
00:13:46,709 --> 00:13:50,623
I am 150 years old, Your Majesty.

171
00:13:52,214 --> 00:13:55,218
In what year were you "borned"?

172
00:13:55,317 --> 00:13:58,958
In 1712, Your Majesty.

173
00:14:03,492 --> 00:14:06,735
How many years
shall you have been married?

174
00:14:06,829 --> 00:14:08,809
Several, Your Majesty.

175
00:14:13,869 --> 00:14:17,681
How many grandchildren shall you have by now?
How many, now many, now many?

176
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:20,151
Ha! You do not
answer that so fast.

177
00:14:20,242 --> 00:14:22,654
I make better question
than she make answer. Ha!

178
00:14:22,745 --> 00:14:25,555
[ Laughing ]

179
00:14:28,684 --> 00:14:31,858
You are not afraid of king.

180
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:35,197
Not to be afraid is good thing
in scientific mind.

181
00:14:36,592 --> 00:14:39,766
I think maybe...

182
00:14:39,862 --> 00:14:42,240
you make very good schoolteaching.

183
00:14:42,331 --> 00:14:44,311
Come!

184
00:14:46,735 --> 00:14:49,375
[ Chattering ]

185
00:14:49,471 --> 00:14:51,451
<i>[ Gong Sounds ]</i>

186
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,961
A few of my wives.

187
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:04,031
They have beauty,
but not gift for knowledge.

188
00:15:04,119 --> 00:15:09,797
I have no time for teaching, being busy
with foreign affairs and other situations.

189
00:15:09,892 --> 00:15:14,637
Ah, I may present
Lady Thiang, head wife.

190
00:15:16,198 --> 00:15:21,079
♪ There is a happy land
far, far away ♪

191
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:27,052
♪ Where saints in glory stand
bright, bright as day ♪ ♪

192
00:15:27,142 --> 00:15:32,023
In the beginning, God created
the heaven and the Earth.

193
00:15:32,114 --> 00:15:34,025
Missionary.

194
00:15:34,116 --> 00:15:36,756
Oh, a missionary
taught you English.

195
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:40,322
Oh, yes, sir. Missionary.

196
00:15:40,422 --> 00:15:42,527
I have boy too-

197
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:46,198
Crown prince Chowfa Chulalongkorn,
heir to throne.

198
00:15:46,295 --> 00:15:49,071
You may help Madam Leonowens
with her schoolteaching...

199
00:15:49,164 --> 00:15:52,145
and she, in her turn,
shall teach you the better English.

200
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:57,616
She is very grateful to me
for my kindness.

201
00:15:57,706 --> 00:16:02,280
Lady Thiang, have children prepare
for presentation to, uh, schoolteacher.

202
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:06,190
Uh- Uh, speaking of teaching,
Your Majesty, in our agreement-

203
00:16:06,281 --> 00:16:08,921
Ah, Lady Son Klin,
Lady Talap, Lady Piam...

204
00:16:09,018 --> 00:16:13,262
and this girl is present to me
from Burma prince.

205
00:16:13,355 --> 00:16:16,097
- She just arrived.
- Good day, madam.

206
00:16:16,191 --> 00:16:18,569
My name is Tuptim.

207
00:16:18,661 --> 00:16:20,902
I already speak English.

208
00:16:20,996 --> 00:16:23,636
And very nicely too.

209
00:16:23,732 --> 00:16:26,372
I think I have fine idea.

210
00:16:26,468 --> 00:16:29,711
In addition to children,
you will also teach those of my wives...

211
00:16:29,805 --> 00:16:31,716
as have sense enough for learning.

212
00:16:31,807 --> 00:16:34,651
Siam to be very modern,
scientific country...

213
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:36,723
everybody speaking the English.

214
00:16:36,812 --> 00:16:41,386
Your Majesty, it is not in our letter of agreement
that I teach your wives too.

215
00:16:41,483 --> 00:16:45,727
Also I will allow you to help me
in my foreign correspondence.

216
00:16:45,821 --> 00:16:48,802
Well, I shall be perfectly happy
to help you in any way I can...

217
00:16:48,891 --> 00:16:52,168
provided we can clear up
this one little matter of the house.

218
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,172
House?

219
00:16:54,263 --> 00:16:57,244
- House? What house?
- Well, my house, Your Majesty-

220
00:16:57,332 --> 00:16:59,437
the one you promised me
adjoining the palace.

221
00:16:59,535 --> 00:17:02,607
It is a pleasure
that you shall live in palace!

222
00:17:02,705 --> 00:17:06,016
You teach in palace,
and you shall live in palace!

223
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:10,079
Will have nice apartment.
Can look out, see many things.

224
00:17:10,179 --> 00:17:12,659
Oh, yes, I'm sure
we could see many things...

225
00:17:12,748 --> 00:17:17,254
such as iron bars, guards at the doors,
et cetera. et cetera. et cetera.

226
00:17:18,387 --> 00:17:20,367
What is this "et cetera"?

227
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:23,562
[ Sighs ]
Well, it means...

228
00:17:23,659 --> 00:17:26,299
"and all the rest and so forth,"
Your Majesty.

229
00:17:26,395 --> 00:17:28,966
- 'Ah
<i>5 ]</i>

230
00:17:29,064 --> 00:17:31,977
- Now you will meet my children.
- I'm very sorry, Your Majesty...

231
00:17:32,067 --> 00:17:35,605
but if there is to be no house, I shall have
to get back to the boat before it sails.

232
00:17:35,704 --> 00:17:39,015
- Come, Louis.
- You will stand here and meet royal children!

233
00:17:44,546 --> 00:17:46,526
Very well, Your Majesty...

234
00:17:47,850 --> 00:17:50,160
but there isn't much time.

235
00:17:50,252 --> 00:17:52,391
<i>[ Gong Sounds ]</i>

236
00:17:55,424 --> 00:17:58,337
The royal princes and princesses.

237
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:40,147
Ah!

238
00:19:22,678 --> 00:19:24,658
[ Shouts In Siamese ]

239
00:19:26,114 --> 00:19:28,890
Ah!

240
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:47,080
[ Siamese ]

241
00:20:17,499 --> 00:20:20,002
Oh!

242
00:20:27,276 --> 00:20:29,256
[ Siamese ]

243
00:21:02,377 --> 00:21:04,618
[ Siamese ]

244
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:31,882
