I gave it to Tuptim.

585
00:43:53,013 --> 00:43:57,393
<i>- The name-you tell me.
- Is call The Small House of Uncle Thomas.</i>

586
00:43:57,484 --> 00:44:00,727
Is by American lady,
Harriet Beecher Stowe.

587
00:44:00,821 --> 00:44:03,392
A woman has written a book?

588
00:44:03,490 --> 00:44:06,937
<i>Uncle Tom's Cabin--
a wonderful book, Your Majesty...</i>

589
00:44:07,027 --> 00:44:09,735
all about the evils of slavery
in America.

590
00:44:09,830 --> 00:44:12,777
Now, President "Lingkong" of America
against slavery, no?

591
00:44:12,866 --> 00:44:16,245
- Very definitely, Your Majesty.
- Me too.

592
00:44:16,337 --> 00:44:20,308
Slavery very bad thing.
[ Sniffs ]

593
00:44:20,407 --> 00:44:24,253
Mr. Lincoln is fighting a war even now
to set the slaves free.

594
00:44:24,345 --> 00:44:26,484
You admire him for this?

595
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:28,491
Very much, Your Majesty.

596
00:44:28,582 --> 00:44:33,224
He seems to be a fine man who has
studied hard and educated himself.

597
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:35,800
In that, he is not unlike yourself.

598
00:44:38,359 --> 00:44:40,270
Ha.

599
00:44:40,361 --> 00:44:43,570
Now, shall "Mr. Lingkong" be winning
this war he's fighting at present?

600
00:44:43,664 --> 00:44:45,644
Well, no one knows really.

601
00:44:45,733 --> 00:44:49,738
Well, does he have enough guns
and elephants for transporting same?

602
00:44:49,837 --> 00:44:53,478
I don't think they have elephants
in America, Your Majesty.

603
00:44:53,574 --> 00:44:55,554
- No elephants?
- No.

604
00:44:55,642 --> 00:44:57,622
No wonder
he is not winning war!

605
00:44:59,680 --> 00:45:02,160
All right, children,
you may be seated now.

606
00:45:07,521 --> 00:45:10,058
- Mrs. Anna?
- Yes, Your Highness?

607
00:45:10,157 --> 00:45:12,296
I do not understand...

608
00:45:12,393 --> 00:45:15,931
how slaves can be set free
if their masters wish to keep them.

609
00:45:16,029 --> 00:45:19,340
It is done by the passing of a law,
Your Highness...

610
00:45:19,433 --> 00:45:22,107
and by the enforcing of that law,
if necessary.

611
00:45:22,202 --> 00:45:26,014
But my slaves
and the slaves of my father-

612
00:45:26,106 --> 00:45:29,349
Suppose there was such a law in Siam,
and we did not want it so.

613
00:45:29,443 --> 00:45:33,858
Sometimes things can't be just a question
of what we want, Your Highness...

614
00:45:33,947 --> 00:45:35,858
but of what is right.

615
00:45:46,226 --> 00:45:48,206
Huh.

616
00:45:50,998 --> 00:45:54,445
I think perhaps we had better call recess now
until after luncheon.

617
00:45:54,535 --> 00:45:57,277
- You may be excused.
- Yea!

618
00:46:17,191 --> 00:46:22,436
Young prince has healthy respect
for ways of his own people-

619
00:46:22,529 --> 00:46:24,975
