Like I see tonight,
in arms of man not her husband?

1453
01:48:00,323 --> 01:48:02,803
- Why, of course.
- I would not permit.

1454
01:48:02,893 --> 01:48:06,136
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, but it's very exciting...

1455
01:48:06,229 --> 01:48:09,972
when you're young,
at your first dance...

1456
01:48:10,066 --> 01:48:14,572
and you're sitting on a small gilt chair
with your eyes lowered...

1457
01:48:15,972 --> 01:48:18,509
<i>terrified that you'll be a wallflower.</i>

1458
01:48:18,608 --> 01:48:23,421
And suddenly you see two black shoes...

1459
01:48:23,513 --> 01:48:26,323
a white waistcoat...

1460
01:48:26,416 --> 01:48:28,794
a face.

1461
01:48:28,885 --> 01:48:30,519
It speaks.

1462
01:48:30,520 --> 01:48:31,089
It speaks.

1463
01:48:31,188 --> 01:48:33,725
♪ We've just be introduced, ♪

1464
01:48:33,823 --> 01:48:36,429
♪ I do not know you well. ♪

1465
01:48:36,526 --> 01:48:38,665
♪ But when the music started, ♪

1466
01:48:38,762 --> 01:48:41,538
♪ something drew me
to your side. ♪

1467
01:48:41,631 --> 01:48:44,077
♪ So many men and girls ♪

1468
01:48:44,167 --> 01:48:46,909
<i>♪ Are in each other's arms, ♪</i>

1469
01:48:47,003 --> 01:48:49,381
♪ It made me think ♪

1470
01:48:49,472 --> 01:48:52,351
♪ we might be ♪

1471
01:48:52,442 --> 01:48:58,085
♪ similarly occupied. ♪

1472
01:48:58,181 --> 01:49:03,631
♪ Shall we dance? ♪

1473
01:49:03,720 --> 01:49:06,200
♪ On a bright cloud of music ♪

1474
01:49:06,289 --> 01:49:08,633
♪ shall we fly? ♪

1475
01:49:08,725 --> 01:49:11,296
♪ Shall we dance? ♪

1476
01:49:11,394 --> 01:49:16,503
♪ Shall we then say "good-night"
and mean "good-bye?" ♪

1477
01:49:16,600 --> 01:49:19,137
♪ Oh, perchance ♪

1478
01:49:19,236 --> 01:49:24,117
♪ when the last little star
has left the sky. ♪

1479
01:49:24,207 --> 01:49:26,881
♪ Shall we still be together ♪

1480
01:49:26,977 --> 01:49:29,150
♪ with our arms around each other, ♪

1481
01:49:29,246 --> 01:49:33,991
♪ And shall you be my new romance? ♪

1482
01:49:34,084 --> 01:49:36,997
♪ On the clear understanding ♪

1483
01:49:37,087 --> 01:49:39,624
♪ that this kind of thing can happen, ♪

1484
01:49:39,723 --> 01:49:42,203
♪ Shall we dance?
Shall we dance? ♪

1485
01:49:42,292 --> 01:49:44,272
♪ Shall we dance? ♪

1486
01:49:57,207 --> 01:49:59,847
Why do you stop? You dance pretty.
Go on, go on, go on.

1487
01:49:59,943 --> 01:50:02,048
Oh, Your Majesty, I didn't realize.

1488
01:50:02,145 --> 01:50:04,352
After all, I'm not a dancing girl.

1489
01:50:04,447 --> 01:50:07,428
In England, no woman would dance alone
while a man is looking at her.

1490
01:50:07,517 --> 01:50:10,157
But she will dance with strange man,
holding hands, et cetera.

1491
01:50:10,253 --> 01:50:13,723
Yes, but not always a stranger.
Usually a very good friend.

1492
01:50:13,823 --> 01:50:16,360
Good. Then we'll dance together.
You show me.

1493
01:50:16,459 --> 01:50:19,235
- Teach, teach, teach!
- Well, it's quite simple, the polka.

1494
01:50:19,329 --> 01:50:22,298
You count, "One, two, three, and one, two, three,
and one, two, three, and"-

1495
01:50:22,299 --> 01:50:24,210
You count, "One, two, three, and one, two, three,
and one, two, three, and"--

1496
01:50:24,301 --> 01:50:26,679
- ♪ Shall we dance? ♪
- One, two, three, and--

1497
01:50:26,770 --> 01:50:28,977
♪ On a bright cloud of music ♪

1498
01:50:29,072 --> 01:50:31,416
- ♪ shall we fly? ♪
- One, two, three, and--

1499
01:50:31,508 --> 01:50:33,818
- ♪ Shall we dance? ♪
- One, two, three, and--

1500
01:50:33,910 --> 01:50:38,586
- ♪ Shall we then say "good-night"
and mean "good-bye?" ♪
- One, two, three, and--

1501
01:50:38,682 --> 01:50:40,889
[ Together ]
♪ Oh, perchance ♪

1502
01:50:40,984 --> 01:50:45,433
♪ when the last little star
has left the sky, ♪

1503
01:50:45,522 --> 01:50:47,900
♪ Shall we still be together ♪

1504
01:50:47,991 --> 01:50:50,301
♪ with our arms around each other, ♪

1505
01:50:50,393 --> 01:50:55,001
- ♪ And shall you be my new romance? ♪
- ♪ Romance ♪

1506
01:50:55,098 --> 01:50:57,374
♪ On the clear understanding ♪

1507
01:50:57,467 --> 01:50:59,674
♪ that this kind of thing can happen, ♪

1508
01:50:59,769 --> 01:51:04,309
♪ Shall we dance? Shall we dance?
Shall we dance? ♪

1509
01:51:04,407 --> 01:51:06,819
- Now, one, two, three, and one, two, three...
- One, two, three.

1510
01:51:06,910 --> 01:51:09,481
- and one, two three.
- One, two, three. One, two--

1511
01:51:09,579 --> 01:51:13,550
Something wrong. I know! I forget "and."
Next time I remember.

1512
01:51:13,650 --> 01:51:15,561
[ Together ]
One, two, three, and one, two, three...

1513
01:51:15,652 --> 01:51:18,223
- and one, two--
- That's splendid, Your Majesty!

1514
01:51:18,321 --> 01:51:20,301
Splendid! Splendid!

1515
01:51:21,424 --> 01:51:24,337
You throw me off count!

1516
01:51:24,427 --> 01:51:28,398
And one, two, three, and one, two, three,
and one, two, three--

1517
01:51:29,866 --> 01:51:31,846
- That is not right.
- Oh, yes, it is.

1518
01:51:31,935 --> 01:51:34,916
- You were doing beautifully, Your Majesty.
- No, no.

1519
01:51:35,004 --> 01:51:37,575
Not the way I see
Europeans dancing tonight.

1520
01:51:37,674 --> 01:51:39,950
Yes, it was.
It was just like that.

1521
01:51:40,043 --> 01:51:43,024
Were not holding
two hands like this.

1522
01:51:48,518 --> 01:51:51,089
No...

1523
01:51:51,187 --> 01:51:53,827
as a matter of fact.

1524
01:51:53,923 --> 01:51:55,903
Was, uh...

1525
01:52:02,365 --> 01:52:04,572
like this...

1526
01:52:04,667 --> 01:52:06,738
no?

1527
01:52:06,836 --> 01:52:09,146
- Yes.
- Come!

1528
01:52:47,010 --> 01:52:50,856
[ Gasps, Panting ]

1529
01:53:06,496 --> 01:53:09,534
Come.
We do it again.

1530
01:53:17,807 --> 01:53:21,220
<i>[ Gong Sounds ]</i>

1531
01:53:22,779 --> 01:53:25,259
- Your Majesty.
- Why do you burst in here without waiting?

1532
01:53:25,348 --> 01:53:27,328
We have found Tuptim.

1533
01:53:29,819 --> 01:53:32,925
- Where is she?
- Secret police are questioning her.

1534
01:53:33,022 --> 01:53:36,595
- Her lover has not been caught-- not yet.
- What?

1535
01:53:36,693 --> 01:53:39,572
It is believed she was running away
with Lun Tha...

1536
01:53:39,662 --> 01:53:42,836
man who bring her here
from Burma.

1537
01:53:42,932 --> 01:53:45,310
Dishonor.

1538
01:53:45,401 --> 01:53:48,041
Dishonor, dishonor!

1539
01:53:48,137 --> 01:53:51,346
- Bring her in!
- But, Your Majesty, what will you do with her?

1540
01:53:51,441 --> 01:53:55,719
- I shall do what is usually done in such event.
- <i>[ Tuptim ] No! No!</i>

1541
01:53:55,812 --> 01:54:00,192
No! Mrs. Anna! Do not let them beat me!
Do not let them!

1542
01:54:00,283 --> 01:54:02,194
- [ Shouts ]
- [ Gasps ]

1543
01:54:02,285 --> 01:54:04,856
- Where is this man?
- I do not know.

1544
01:54:04,954 --> 01:54:07,264
It is known you were lovers
with this man.

1545
01:54:07,357 --> 01:54:10,702
- I was not lovers with this man!
- Dishonor.

1546
01:54:10,793 --> 01:54:12,864
[ Shouts ]
Will have truth of you!

1547
01:54:12,962 --> 01:54:15,875
Stop that! Do you hear me?
Stop it!

1548
01:54:15,965 --> 01:54:18,445
It is better if you understand at once...

1549
01:54:18,535 --> 01:54:20,845
that this matter does not
concern you.

1550
01:54:20,937 --> 01:54:22,917
Oh, but it does, Your Majesty.

1551
01:54:23,006 --> 01:54:26,977
It does dreadfully because of her,
and even more, because of you.

1552
01:54:27,076 --> 01:54:30,057
She's only a child running away
because she was unhappy.

1553
01:54:30,146 --> 01:54:33,093
- Can't you understand that?
- You waste my time!

1554
01:54:33,182 --> 01:54:36,322
<i>Oh, Your Majesty, I beg of you
not to take revenge on this girl.</i>

1555
01:54:36,419 --> 01:54:39,400
If you do, you will be throwing away
everything good you have accomplished...

1556
01:54:39,489 --> 01:54:41,400
for yourself and your country.

1557
01:54:41,491 --> 01:54:44,870
This girl hurt your vanity. That is all.
She didn't hurt your heart.

1558
01:54:44,961 --> 01:54:49,376
You have no heart! You've never loved anyone,
and you never will.

1559
01:54:49,465 --> 01:54:51,376
I will show you! Give me.

1560
01:54:51,467 --> 01:54:54,004
I cannot believe you are going to do
this dreadful thing!

1561
01:54:54,103 --> 01:54:57,880
You don't believe, huh? Maybe you believe when
you hear her screaming as you run from here.

1562
01:54:57,974 --> 01:55:01,945
I am not going to run.
I am going to stand here and watch you.

1563
01:55:02,045 --> 01:55:04,082
Hold this girl.
I do this myself!

1564
01:55:04,180 --> 01:55:08,424
- You <i>are</i> a barbarian!
- Down, down, down!

1565
01:55:08,518 --> 01:55:10,429
[ Gasping ]

1566
01:55:10,520 --> 01:55:13,091
Am I king
or am I not king?

1567
01:55:13,189 --> 01:55:15,965
Am I to be cuckold
in my own palace?

1568
01:55:16,059 --> 01:55:18,198
Am I to take orders
from English schoolteacher?

1569
01:55:18,294 --> 01:55:20,274
- No, no. Not orders!
- Silence!

1570
01:55:20,363 --> 01:55:23,537
I am king,
as I was born to be...

1571
01:55:23,633 --> 01:55:26,341
and Siam to be governed
in my way!

1572
01:55:26,436 --> 01:55:29,110
Not English way, not French way,
not Chinese way!

1573
01:55:29,205 --> 01:55:31,242
My way!

1574
01:55:31,341 --> 01:55:33,787
Barbarian, you say?

1575
01:55:33,876 --> 01:55:36,880
There is no barbarian
worse than a weak king.

1576
01:55:36,980 --> 01:55:38,982
And I am strong, do you hear?

1577
01:55:39,082 --> 01:55:41,528
- Strong!
- [ Gasps ]

1578
01:56:03,272 --> 01:56:06,742
- Well?
- The man, the lover, has been found in river.

1579
01:56:06,843 --> 01:56:08,754
- He is dead.
- [ Gasps ]

1580
01:56:08,845 --> 01:56:11,485
Dead? Oh, no!

1581
01:56:11,581 --> 01:56:14,858
- Aah!
- [ Crying ] Oh, no!

1582
01:56:14,951 --> 01:56:17,898
[ Sobbing ]
Oh, no!

1583
01:56:17,987 --> 01:56:19,898
<i>[ Sobbing Continues ]</i>

1584
01:56:19,989 --> 01:56:23,459
I don't understand you--
not you or your king.

1585
01:56:23,559 --> 01:56:27,006
- I'll never understand him.
- You--

1586
01:56:27,096 --> 01:56:31,101
When I warn you of this many months ago,
you do not listen.

1587
01:56:31,200 --> 01:56:33,578
- You have destroyed him.
- Oh.

1588
01:56:33,670 --> 01:56:36,310
He can never be the king
that he was before.

1589
01:56:36,406 --> 01:56:39,944
You have taken all that away from him.
You have destroyed king!

1590
01:56:40,043 --> 01:56:44,048
The next boat that comes here, no matter
where it goes, I shall be on it.

1591
01:56:46,482 --> 01:56:49,122
Give this back to His Majesty.

1592
01:56:49,218 --> 01:56:52,097
I wish you have never come to Siam!

1593
01:56:52,188 --> 01:56:56,159
So do I! Oh, so do I!

1594
01:56:56,259 --> 01:56:58,493
[ Crying ]

1595
01:56:58,494 --> 01:56:59,131
[ Crying ]

1596
01:56:59,228 --> 01:57:03,438
[ Horn Blowing ]

1597
01:57:37,633 --> 01:57:40,671
<i>[ Children, Wives ]
♪ Getting to know you ♪</i>

1598
01:57:40,770 --> 01:57:45,344
<i>♪ Putting it my way but nicely, ♪</i>

1599
01:57:45,441 --> 01:57:48,388
<i>♪ You are precisely ♪</i>

1600
01:57:48,478 --> 01:57:51,789
<i>- ♪ My cup of tea! ♪ ♪
- [ Louis ] Mother!</i>

1601
01:57:51,881 --> 01:57:54,361
Mother, our luggage is all loaded.

1602
01:57:54,450 --> 01:57:57,090
We'll be late for the boat.

1603
01:57:57,186 --> 01:57:59,826
Yes, Louis. I'm coming.

1604
01:58:04,560 --> 01:58:07,541
- Mrs. Anna.
- <i>Lady Thiang.</i>

1605
01:58:07,630 --> 01:58:11,669
<i>Your Highness, how nice of you
to come to say good-bye.</i>

1606
01:58:11,768 --> 01:58:14,442
Mrs. Anna,
I do not come for myself.

1607
01:58:14,537 --> 01:58:17,848
I come for one
who must see you quickly.

1608
01:58:17,940 --> 01:58:21,080
You may tell His Majesty
I am no longer subject to his commands.

1609
01:58:21,177 --> 01:58:23,817
You do not understand.

1610
01:58:23,913 --> 01:58:27,122
Mrs. Anna, he is dying.

1611
01:58:29,118 --> 01:58:32,827
Dying? The king?

1612
01:58:32,922 --> 01:58:35,994
Oh, no, Lady Thiang.
What-- What happened?

1613
01:58:37,393 --> 01:58:41,705
Who can say what it is
that makes a man die?

1614
01:58:41,798 --> 01:58:46,269
A sad heart that no longer wishes
to go on beating?

1615
01:58:46,369 --> 01:58:48,610
Ever since night of great banquet...

1616
01:58:48,704 --> 01:58:51,014
he has shut himself away
in palace...

1617
01:58:51,107 --> 01:58:53,348
turning from all
who would speak to him...

1618
01:58:53,442 --> 01:58:57,413
unwilling to sleep
or to nourish himself...

1619
01:58:57,513 --> 01:59:01,620
searching through many books,
only to push them aside in despair.

1620
01:59:02,985 --> 01:59:07,195
Doctors warned him
he must change his ways quickly...

1621
01:59:07,290 --> 01:59:10,965
but he would not listen,
Mrs. Anna.

1622
01:59:11,060 --> 01:59:13,199
He would not listen.

1623
01:59:13,296 --> 01:59:15,207
I had no idea.

1624
01:59:15,298 --> 01:59:19,610
Everyone who knew was
forbidden to speak of it.

1625
01:59:20,736 --> 01:59:24,684
And now doctors have
no hope for him.

1626
01:59:24,774 --> 01:59:25,140
<i>Mrs. Anna?</i>

1627
01:59:25,141 --> 01:59:26,677
<i>Mrs. Anna?</i>

1628
01:59:26,776 --> 01:59:30,553
- <i>[ Anna ] Your Highness.</i>
- I am frightened, Mrs. Anna.

1629
01:59:30,646 --> 01:59:33,456
I am frightened
because I love my father...

1630
01:59:33,549 --> 01:59:38,089
and also because if he dies,
I shall be king...

1631
01:59:38,187 --> 01:59:40,565
and I do not know how to be.

1632
01:59:40,656 --> 01:59:42,795
Oh.

1633
01:59:42,892 --> 01:59:47,671
Many men learn this after they
become kings, Your Highness.

1634
01:59:47,763 --> 01:59:50,141
It will be good to think back...

1635
01:59:50,233 --> 01:59:53,214
on all that Mrs. Anna has taught you.

1636
01:59:56,105 --> 02:00:00,417
When king heard you were sailing tonight,
he started to write letter.

1637
02:00:00,509 --> 02:00:03,888
It was difficult for him,
Mrs. Anna.

1638
02:00:03,980 --> 02:00:06,426
Very difficult.

1639
02:00:06,515 --> 02:00:09,985
He has commanded
that I give it to you.

1640
02:00:17,693 --> 02:00:21,937
Please, may I hear what my father has said,
Mrs. Anna?

1641
02:00:35,044 --> 02:00:37,388
"While I am lying here...

1642
02:00:37,480 --> 02:00:40,484
"I think, perhaps, I die.

1643
02:00:40,583 --> 02:00:43,325
"This heart, which you say
I have not got...

1644
02:00:43,419 --> 02:00:46,559
"is matter of concern.

1645
02:00:46,656 --> 02:00:49,535
"It occurs to me
that there shall be nothing wrong...

1646
02:00:49,625 --> 02:00:51,764
"that men shall die...

1647
02:00:51,861 --> 02:00:54,068
"for all that matters about man...

1648
02:00:54,163 --> 02:00:58,634
"is that he shall have tried
his utmost best.

1649
02:00:58,734 --> 02:01:01,442
"In looking back,
I discover that you think much...

1650
02:01:01,537 --> 02:01:03,608
<i>"on those people...</i>

1651
02:01:03,706 --> 02:01:06,550
<i>"who require that you live up
to best of self.</i>

1652
02:01:08,110 --> 02:01:11,580
"You have spoken truth
to me always...

1653
02:01:11,681 --> 02:01:16,289
"and for this I have often
lost my temper on you.

1654
02:01:16,385 --> 02:01:18,365
"But now I do not wish to die...

1655
02:01:18,454 --> 02:01:22,402
"without saying this gratitude...

1656
02:01:22,491 --> 02:01:24,471
"and large respect...

1657
02:01:24,560 --> 02:01:27,598
"et cetera, et cetera.

1658
02:01:27,697 --> 02:01:30,177
"I think it very strange
that a woman...

1659
02:01:30,266 --> 02:01:34,078
"shall have been
most earnest help of all.

1660
02:01:34,170 --> 02:01:36,446
"But, Mrs. Anna,
you must remember...

1661
02:01:36,539 --> 02:01:40,749
"that you have been
a very difficult woman...

1662
02:01:40,843 --> 02:01:44,814
and much more difficult
than generality."

1663
02:01:44,914 --> 02:01:46,894
[ Sobbing ]

1664
02:01:48,985 --> 02:01:50,965
We must hurry back now.

1665
02:01:52,621 --> 02:01:54,601
You will come?

1666
02:02:19,115 --> 02:02:22,858
Mother, now that the king is dying...

1667
02:02:22,952 --> 02:02:25,831
does that make you friends again?

1668
02:02:25,921 --> 02:02:28,299
I suppose so, Louis.

1669
02:02:28,391 --> 02:02:32,032
We can't hurt each other anymore.

1670
02:02:32,128 --> 02:02:34,108
He always frightened me.

1671
02:02:35,498 --> 02:02:37,478
I wish you had known him better.

1672
02:02:37,566 --> 02:02:40,945
You two could have been
such good friends.

1673
02:02:41,037 --> 02:02:45,918
In many ways, he was just as young as you.
[ Sniffles ]

1674
02:02:46,008 --> 02:02:49,615
Was he as good a king
as he could have been?

1675
02:02:51,080 --> 02:02:54,084
I don't think any man has ever been
as good a king...

1676
02:02:54,183 --> 02:02:56,595
as he could have been.

1677
02:02:56,685 --> 02:02:59,165
But this one tried.

1678
02:02:59,255 --> 02:03:01,394
He tried very hard.

1679
02:03:04,293 --> 02:03:07,433
You really like him,
don't you, Mother?

1680
02:03:07,530 --> 02:03:09,771
Yes, Louis.

1681
02:03:09,865 --> 02:03:12,778
I like him very much.

1682
02:03:12,868 --> 02:03:14,848
Very much indeed.

1683
02:03:17,706 --> 02:03:22,348
♪ ♪ [ Quiet Singing In Siamese ]

1684
02:03:47,236 --> 02:03:50,911
Several weeks I do not see you,
Mrs. Anna.

1685
02:03:52,508 --> 02:03:54,510
And now I die.

1686
02:03:54,610 --> 02:03:56,590
Oh, no, Your Majesty.

1687
02:03:56,679 --> 02:03:59,285
This is not scientific.

1688
02:04:00,649 --> 02:04:04,961
I know if I die or do not die.

1689
02:04:05,054 --> 02:04:08,433
You shouldn't be here.
Can't we move you to your room?

1690
02:04:08,524 --> 02:04:10,629
No.

1691
02:04:10,726 --> 02:04:14,003
I wish to remain here
in room with knowledge.

1692
02:04:17,266 --> 02:04:19,974
You are leaving Siam?

1693
02:04:20,069 --> 02:04:23,209
- When?
- Very soon, Your Majesty.

1694
02:04:23,305 --> 02:04:26,081
In fact, I can stay
only a few more minutes.

1695
02:04:26,175 --> 02:04:29,156
And you are glad of this?

1696
02:04:29,245 --> 02:04:31,452
People of Siam--

1697
02:04:31,547 --> 02:04:33,857
royal children, et cetera--

1698
02:04:33,949 --> 02:04:35,860
are not glad.

1699
02:04:35,951 --> 02:04:40,263
And all are in great affliction...

1700
02:04:40,356 --> 02:04:42,336
of your departure.

1701
02:04:44,059 --> 02:04:45,970
I shall miss them.

1702
02:04:46,061 --> 02:04:49,873
You shall miss them,
but you shall be leaving.

1703
02:04:53,068 --> 02:04:56,515
I, too, am leaving...

1704
02:04:56,605 --> 02:05:00,747
only I'm not walking onto a boat
with my own feet...

1705
02:05:00,843 --> 02:05:03,084
of my own free will.

1706
02:05:06,248 --> 02:05:08,228
I am just leaving.

1707
02:05:10,753 --> 02:05:13,791
Why is your head higher than mine?

1708
02:05:21,330 --> 02:05:23,241
Here.

1709
02:05:25,434 --> 02:05:28,415
Here is something
belonging to you.

1710
02:05:28,504 --> 02:05:30,415
Put it on.

1711
02:05:30,506 --> 02:05:33,112
Put it on, put it on!

1712
02:05:34,410 --> 02:05:37,391
Please, wear it.

1713
02:05:49,592 --> 02:05:51,503
The children.

1714
02:05:54,029 --> 02:05:56,168
Let my children come in.

1715
02:06:06,075 --> 02:06:08,214
Good evening, children.

1716
02:06:08,310 --> 02:06:10,449
Good evening, my father.

1717
02:06:10,546 --> 02:06:12,924
- Please, Mrs. Anna, do not go!
- [ All Clamoring ]

1718
02:06:13,015 --> 02:06:15,996
Children, stop this noise.

1719
02:06:16,085 --> 02:06:18,964
Did you come to see your father
or Mrs. Anna?

1720
02:06:19,054 --> 02:06:21,091
It is all right, Lady Thiang.

1721
02:06:21,190 --> 02:06:23,057
It is suitable.

1722
02:06:23,058 --> 02:06:23,331
It is suitable.

1723
02:06:23,425 --> 02:06:26,634
My father?

1724
02:06:26,729 --> 02:06:28,800
Princess Ying Yaowalak?

1725
02:06:28,897 --> 02:06:31,468
I have wish to--

1726
02:06:33,702 --> 02:06:36,546
She has memorized message
for Mrs. Anna.

1727
02:06:36,639 --> 02:06:39,483
Speak message now.

1728
02:06:42,344 --> 02:06:44,255
<i>Say it, say it, say it.</i>

1729
02:06:44,346 --> 02:06:47,293
Dear friend and teacher...

1730
02:06:47,383 --> 02:06:50,296
my goodness gracious...

1731
02:06:50,386 --> 02:06:52,923
do not go away.

1732
02:06:53,022 --> 02:06:55,764
We are in great need of you.

1733
02:06:55,858 --> 02:06:58,702
<i>We are like one blind</i>

1734
02:06:58,794 --> 02:07:02,173
<i>Do not let us fall down in darkness.</i>

1735
02:07:02,264 --> 02:07:07,373
Continue good and sincere concern...

1736
02:07:07,469 --> 02:07:09,380
for us...

1737
02:07:09,471 --> 02:07:11,473
and lead us in right road.

1738
02:07:11,573 --> 02:07:13,553
Your loving pupil...

1739
02:07:13,642 --> 02:07:16,782
Princess Ying Yaowalak.

1740
02:07:22,418 --> 02:07:24,694
[ Crying ]

1741
02:07:24,787 --> 02:07:29,065
<i>[ Ship Horn Blows ]</i>

1742
02:07:29,158 --> 02:07:31,832
Mother, it's the boat.

1743
02:07:31,927 --> 02:07:34,669
- It's time to go.
- Do not go, Mrs. Anna!

1744
02:07:34,763 --> 02:07:36,970
- Please do not go!
- No, no, Mrs. Anna!

1745
02:07:37,066 --> 02:07:40,878
<i>[ Horn Blows ]</i>

1746
02:07:54,483 --> 02:07:57,726
<i>[ Horn Blowing ]</i>

1747
02:07:57,820 --> 02:08:01,996
Louis, run down to the boat and ask Captain
Orton to take our things off and send them back.

1748
02:08:02,091 --> 02:08:04,071
<i>[ Louis ] Yes, Mother.</i>

1749
02:08:08,330 --> 02:08:10,401
[ Cheering ]

1750
02:08:10,499 --> 02:08:12,410
Silence!

1751
02:08:14,303 --> 02:08:17,807
There is no reason
for doing of demonstration...

1752
02:08:17,906 --> 02:08:21,046
for schoolteacher
realizing her duty...

1753
02:08:21,143 --> 02:08:25,785
for which I pay her
exorbitant monthly fee...

1754
02:08:25,881 --> 02:08:27,792
of, uh--

1755
02:08:28,917 --> 02:08:32,262
of £25.

1756
02:08:32,354 --> 02:08:36,063
- [ All ] Ooh!
<i>- Furthermore...</i>

1757
02:08:37,659 --> 02:08:41,607
this is disorganized behavior...

1758
02:08:42,765 --> 02:08:45,371
in presence of dying king.

1759
02:08:47,503 --> 02:08:49,483
Chulalongkorn.

1760
02:08:50,806 --> 02:08:52,717
Rise.

1761
02:08:54,042 --> 02:08:55,953
Mrs. Anna...

1762
02:08:57,613 --> 02:09:00,594
you take notes.

1763
02:09:04,019 --> 02:09:05,999
You take notes...

1764
02:09:07,956 --> 02:09:10,129
from next king.

1765
02:09:11,994 --> 02:09:14,873
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

1766
02:09:16,799 --> 02:09:20,542
Well, suppose you are king.

1767
02:09:20,636 --> 02:09:23,116
Is there nothing you would do?

1768
02:09:23,205 --> 02:09:27,449
I--I would make proclamations.

1769
02:09:27,543 --> 02:09:29,853
Yes? Yes?

1770
02:09:29,945 --> 02:09:34,587
First, I would proclaim
for coming New Year, fireworks.

1771
02:09:34,683 --> 02:09:36,629
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

1772
02:09:36,718 --> 02:09:38,629
Also boat races.

1773
02:09:38,720 --> 02:09:41,030
Boat races?

1774
02:09:41,123 --> 02:09:44,366
Why boat races
with New Year's celebration?

1775
02:09:45,527 --> 02:09:47,666
I like boat races.

1776
02:09:47,763 --> 02:09:50,573
And, Father, I would make
second proclamation.

1777
02:09:50,666 --> 02:09:53,647
Yes, what is second proclamation?
Make it, make it.

1778
02:09:53,735 --> 02:09:56,272
Regarding custom of bowing to king...

1779
02:09:56,371 --> 02:09:59,147
in fashion of lowly toad...

1780
02:10:00,242 --> 02:10:02,722
I do not believe
this is good thing...

1781
02:10:02,811 --> 02:10:05,291
causing embarrassing fatigue of body...

1782
02:10:05,380 --> 02:10:07,860
degrading experience for soul...

1783
02:10:07,950 --> 02:10:09,930
et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.

1784
02:10:10,018 --> 02:10:11,998
This is bad thing...

1785
02:10:13,188 --> 02:10:15,327
I... believe.

1786
02:10:20,729 --> 02:10:23,835
You are angry at me, my father?

1787
02:10:23,932 --> 02:10:27,436
Oh, why do you ask question?

1788
02:10:28,470 --> 02:10:30,381
If you are king...

1789
02:10:31,473 --> 02:10:34,010
you are <i>king.</i>

1790
02:10:35,611 --> 02:10:38,091
Do not ask question of sick man...

1791
02:10:40,148 --> 02:10:44,119
nor of woman.

1792
02:10:44,219 --> 02:10:47,564
This proclamation...

1793
02:10:47,656 --> 02:10:50,762
against bowing to king...

1794
02:10:50,859 --> 02:10:54,671
I believe to be your fault.

1795
02:10:56,265 --> 02:10:59,576
Oh, I hope so, Your Majesty.

1796
02:10:59,668 --> 02:11:01,648
I do hope so.

1797
02:11:03,605 --> 02:11:05,585
Up! Rise up.

1798
02:11:10,279 --> 02:11:12,190
Father?

1799
02:11:13,415 --> 02:11:15,861
Up, up, up.

1800
02:11:15,951 --> 02:11:18,591
Like soldiers, into lines.

1801
02:11:22,124 --> 02:11:24,104
It has been said.

1802
02:11:25,294 --> 02:11:27,774
There shall be no more bowing...

1803
02:11:29,531 --> 02:11:32,910
for showing <i>respect...</i>

1804
02:11:34,102 --> 02:11:36,013
for king.

1805
02:11:40,742 --> 02:11:43,052
It has been said by one...

1806
02:11:45,814 --> 02:11:48,886
who has been trained...

1807
02:11:48,984 --> 02:11:52,625
for royal government.

1808
02:11:56,058 --> 02:11:58,163
[ Sighs ]

1809
02:12:06,435 --> 02:12:08,915
There shall be no bowing like toad.

1810
02:12:09,004 --> 02:12:12,042
No crouching, no crawling.

1811
02:12:12,140 --> 02:12:14,120
This does not mean, however...

1812
02:12:14,209 --> 02:12:16,450
that you do not show respect for king.

1813
02:12:16,545 --> 02:12:19,492
<i>You will stand with shoulders back...</i>

1814
02:12:19,581 --> 02:12:22,289
- <i>and chin high, like this.</i>
- [ Sighs ]

1815
02:12:22,384 --> 02:12:25,729
<i>You will face king
with proud expression...</i>

1816
02:12:25,821 --> 02:12:29,462
<i>showing pride in self
as well as in king.</i>

1817
02:12:29,558 --> 02:12:31,392
This is proper way for men
to show esteem for one another-

1818
02:12:31,393 --> 02:12:34,033
This is proper way for men
to show esteem for one another--

1819
02:12:34,129 --> 02:12:36,609
by looking upon each other's faces...

1820
02:12:36,698 --> 02:12:38,678
with calmness of spirit...

1821
02:12:38,767 --> 02:12:41,475
eyes meeting eyes in equal gaze...

1822
02:12:41,570 --> 02:12:44,176
bodies upright, standing as men
were meant to stand-

1823
02:12:44,272 --> 02:12:48,652
- [ Continues, Indistinct ]
<i>- [ Chorus ] ♪ He'll always need your love, ♪</i>

1824
02:12:48,744 --> 02:12:51,190
So, from this day forward--

1825
02:12:51,279 --> 02:12:57,230
<i>♪ And so he'll get your love. ♪</i>

1826
02:12:57,319 --> 02:13:03,634
<i>♪ A man who needs your love ♪</i>

1827
02:13:03,725 --> 02:13:06,763
<i>♪ can be ♪</i>

1828
02:13:06,862 --> 02:13:16,476
<i>♪ wonderful ♪ ♪</i>
